	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories A suspect has been ben arrested and charged with the murder of Irish charity worker John Curran, Western Cape police confirmed on Saturday. The 24-year-old man was arrested in Voortrekker Road on Friday night following “thorough investigation”, spokesperson Sergeant Noloyiso Rwexana said. Detectives followed up on leads and a suspect was circulated, resulting in the man being apprehended and charged with murder. Curran was murdered at a high-security residential complex in Buitengracht Street, Cape Town just over two weeks ago. The 60-year-old had recently finished a two-year contract as a director of education for Mellon Educate in South Africa. The charity at the time in a statement said that Curran was killed during a robbery. Curran was found in a pool of blood and had open wounds to his head and face, police had said. READ: Irish aid worker murdered in Cape Town 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  